Review: The experience here was good. All veg subs (6 inch) are priced at ₹250 irrespective of which one we take. The customer service was friendly and most importantly, place was hygienic. Another thing to be appreciated is that they have separate counters for veg and non-veg which we don't find in many other subway outlets.

Foods are not fresh and it is much upscale as per cost. Variety are sufficient available. Location is prime, exactly at International Airport Bangalore. Outside sitting arrangement ate there and very good ambience. If your flight is delayed or you visited for receiving someone and waiting, it is good place to pass time happily.
Service is quite fast..Take away is available..

Rates are higher. They are charging according to the USA standard. It need to be charged according to Indian standard. Cost of production of raw material is very less even though they are charging higher-ups. Subway cleanelesniss is good and well maintained.

Most of the time I find this as closed or under renovation.
Now probably due to ongoing situation but earlier too.
Or may be my visit n their downtime coincides.

When I’m on early morning flight to Bangalore. This happens to be my first place to eat and relax before staying a day. The Restaurent is very nice & service is very fast. Sometime they don’t have hot beverages. My favorite is chicken salad
Nice eatery in airport.

Very nice spot for subway on your way out of the airport 

Good food quick service too tasty stuff

Very pathetic approach of customer dealing. I have told to be in line and order. I ordered and waited for 10 minutes...They gave my order to someone else.
And after doing this they have shown any courtesy.

During late night and early morning flights, I usually chill here before entering the airport. The employees are pretty friendly and quick. You will get your order in your hand in two minutes no matter how crowded the spot is.
Standard subway like all other subway. Service is slow. Veg products are not good
Always been a family favourite. Love how one can make their own sandwich according to one’s preferencces.
Good quality of edibles

Very distracted people at work.
A couple of times got burned bread instead of toasted.
Otherwise it's a simple Subway experience.
Dorsnt have 'sub of the day'.
Huge portion of food...average taste
It was a good experience for me, in terms of both the taste and the service. One of the employee, Mr Jayakrishnan was courteous and polite in his service.

It was good experience, staff was nice but little confused with order billing, I think it's because not proper channel of communication between them.
I had panner tikka sandwich with roasted garlic bread, loved it.
Overall good experience.

Service is bad and the food served is no different either. Price charged is a lot more than what one would think the whole experience is worth.
Unhygienic. Very low service standards of the staff and the sandwiches for some reason tastes worse than other outlets. Wonder how this place has continued to be open despite the standards remaining at a very subpar level since as far as it has been around.
As good as few other options available
Be careful. I purchased 2 bottles of water and one was open beforehand. Check at time of purchase. They did exchange.
Food they serve is good but the service given by the lady at the cash counter is very bad. Subway should give training to her on "How to deal with the customers"

Worst sub ever... No fresh vegetables, ingredients .. everything is so dry. Don't ever waste your money. 
No taste... Nothing... Totally disappointed
Food is always good. Price is a lil high

Very tasty both veg and non veg sandwiches are sold here. The bread, spread, vegetables, and sauce of our choice is in preparing the sandwich.  Be prepared to answer the questions at counter!!☺️
The size is uncomfortable and difficult to eat many times.  It is a mess in the end!!
Taste was good.  Very convenient to eat while traveling.  Price is exorbitant!!!.

A lot of improvement needed. I bought two foot long sandwiches and asked for them to be toasted. One was toasted too much while the other was cold. The lettuce was dry and old. 
In spite of asking repeatedly not to add some of the ingredients, the person preparing the sandwich for me just turned a deaf ear. This could be due to the fatigue of working long hours because when I got here, it was 2 am. But that should not stop them from serving food at a better quality. The sauce was messy and the packaging was too poor for their standards of customer service.
Traveling from the US, I felt the quality of Subway in India is below par and needs more improvements if they want to stay float in the food industry. I feel it will be better if Subway is inside the Airport and not outside the gates

Bad experience. I ordered veggy patty and they dint add the patty only in the burger. Not hygienic..they were adding the cabbage which were falling on the floor.. Don't know to handle customers. Very rude.. Talking behind the back in the regional language in the billing section.. Wasting time..not at all kind..my money was wasted.. Please remove such people from billing counter if they are taking their job so lightly and not responsible
Nice
Outlet at the entrance of the airport, has different sections for veg and non veg

Worst experience I ever had at subway. Three people made 1 single sandwich. Extra cheese added without asking. Used Mustard instead of south west. Served me a sandwich and tea without tray. Staff is untrained.
Pathetic training Bad experience
It's just another Subway but I like it more than the others. Service is really good. And the food they serve is really fresh.

Service is 24*7 which is something to appreciate. These guys work hard with a smile on their face and they make great sandwiches. I am highly satisfied with the quantity and quality. He made it the way i asked him to make which is quite rare. Please keep an eye on the freshness of the ingredients as a customer who was ahead of me had a complaint related to it.
Quality was good, not proper guidance for first time customer

Not a big fan of this place. The airport stall is always crowded. the subs are just at par. As soon as you walk out of the exit there are many stalls for ex hatti kappi, chai point for beverages. Street foods by Punjabi grills for some Indian food. Krispy Kreme for doughnuts.

This outlet is just ok.

Pathetic service. Staff did not pick up toasted bread from oven till I reminded them, not under staffed , but people at this outlet did not want to work . No common sense -without asking/ waiting for my conformation randomly put  some dressings . Never had such bad experience at any subway outlet. When I asked for manager , to speak with him -he did not bother to converse.

On the first day we arrived in the Bangalore, I and my friends were soo hungry and saw this Subway outlet at the arrivals and reached there. We are shocked with the very first point, the price which was more than double the price followed at the other outlets of Subway, but why is it so, what makes so much of a difference. With such a high price and higher percentage of taxation they didn't maintain the fest stock but prepared the sub from the frozen ingredients. And this outlet is completely open to atmosphere with no special air-conditioning and the seating available there were not sufficient and those were not cleaned properly every now and then. The soiled plates of the previous customers were left on the tables though many are waiting to get seated if they were cleaned. When informed at the counter they have no intention of paying attention for the complaint I wanted to say. The airport authority shall not allow the prices to be hiked to the sky, if not, no normal could be able to afford.
deliceous burger,nice preparation,you can choose your topping seeing them being prepared..
It is one of the outlet of Subway just within the airport complex. Vegan food available. Lot of seating available. Good preparation, quick service.
Nice and good food
Good place
Fresh food for a reasonable price

Had ordered for Chicken Tikka sub but the chicken had weird mushy texture and also didn't taste anything like chicken tikka.. Didn't feel like going back to the counter and return it as the cashier was very rude and had refused to give employee discount even after presenting the ID... The attitude of staff and quality of food at Subway is depriciating day by day..

The Bengaluru international airport subway cashier was not learned enough to handle the customers. He wasn't giving attention to the orders and had billed wrong to me. On saying, he back answered me saying I wasn't clear. He was not ready to listen to my order. 
I love subway and always had a awesome experience and i am one of the frequent visitor to subway. This is the first time such a awful experience.

Extremely pathetic service. No coordination between the serving and billing staff. They were mixing up most of the orders. My order was prepared within 10 minutes, but then I had to wait for 32 more minutes in the billing queue though there were only 4 customers before me in the queue. Average time for billing one customer was almost 9 minutes!!! Only one person was handling the billing. None of the 4 card readers seemed to be working fine. Finally after spending 42 minutes and with orders still mixed up, I just left without taking my order. At such a busy place, they should train multiple people to handle the billing. Didn't want to give even one-star rating. They were definitely zero today. Not going to come back to this outlet ever.

Worst subway ever...been waiting here to order for 20min
No one ever cares to take orders
Food is not fresh
Cost is expensive than other subways as it is in airport. Taste was bad  and it will always have a queue ! two 6-inch veg subs cost me 900 rupees! this is insane !

The tomato slices look stale and there was hair in the subway. There is no professionalism in the people who manage the counter
Some sause were not there .. and it cost 75% more than normal!!
Best quality and too much costly
Airport Subway is best stop for a having a nice Sandwiches at the normal cost, compared to other food joints in airport which costs so much high than normal restaurants.

Poor customer service. No attentive staff. No care for hygiene. Floor was being wept during preparation / service. 
The lady was rude to let me know of an option that wasn't available. Didn't bother to check the bread options.
Being in airport they should understand how important each minute is. They'll happily make you miss your flight. Slow service. Average subs.
Pathetic Place. I found Bug inside the Bread. Don't eat at all her. Even if you are hungry. It's like risking your life

Past 10 Years I'm subway customer, never had a bad experience but this is Very bad food prep, customer service is also like food they have vegetables are not at all fresh, bread is not fresh and very dry. subway should be take responsible for this type of ripoffs.

Not good experience, extremely unattentive stuff. To me it looks like they (the org) do not change their shifts on regular basis and thus  some are stretching beyond hours or are just not used to with any kind of night shift. Unless YOU are careful and attentive you sub may become something really "sub-standard" 🤨
Rates were much higher than other subways in the country.  Almost double
Good sub.. The employees need training...the employees easily get irritated.. Not ready to answer questions..
Typical Subway with good food standards and friendly staff. Its outside the airport and very slow service. Seating is limited. Ideal for light snacks before traveling

Ordered 4 teas and was disappointed. They kept me waiting and after we got the teas found it lukewarm and lousy. Not worth money spent. Complained and they glossed over it as though they will pass feedback. One of the lousiest Subway joint in Bengaluru.
